            new Query("query1"), List.of(List.of(new Document("doc1", 0.9)), List.of(new Document("doc3", 0.7))),
            new Query("query2"), List.of(List.of(new Document("doc2", 0.8)), List.of(new Document("doc1", 0.6))) //doc1 is duplicate
        );

        // Create a DocumentJoiner (using ConcatenationDocumentJoiner in this example)
        DocumentJoiner documentJoiner = new ConcatenationDocumentJoiner();

        // Join the documents
        List<Document> joinedDocuments = documentJoiner.join(documentsForQuery);

        // Print the joined documents
        for (Document doc : joinedDocuments) {
            System.out.println("Document ID: " + doc.getId() + ", Score: " + doc.getScore());
        }
    }
}

// Define necessary classes (Query and Document) for the example to compile
class Query {
    private String text;

    public Query(String text) {
        this.text = text;
    }

    public String getText() {
        return text;
    }
}

class Document {
    private String id;
    private Double score;

    public Document(String id, Double score) {
        this.id = id;
        this.score = score;
    }

    public String getId() {
        return id;
    }

    public Double getScore() {
        return score;
    }
}
```

This example demonstrates how to use the `ConcatenationDocumentJoiner` to combine documents retrieved from multiple queries.  It creates a sample `documentsForQuery` map, instantiates a `ConcatenationDocumentJoiner`, calls the `join` method, and then prints the IDs and scores of the resulting joined documents.  The `ConcatenationDocumentJoiner` will concatenate the lists of documents, keeping only the first occurrence of any duplicate documents, and sort the final list by score in descending order.

